But we need to have the trigger be the button that opens the modal. So we need to wrap the button in DialogTrigger. But we have multiple buttons across cards. We can have each button be a DialogTrigger that points to the same Dialog component? That would cause multiple Dialog components. Better to have a single Dialog component that is conditionally rendered when a movie is selected. The trigger can be a custom component that receives the movie and sets state.

Simplify: In each card, we have a button with onClick that sets selectedMovie and isModalOpen. Then we render a Dialog component at top-level that uses the selectedMovie and isModalOpen. The button itself is not a DialogTrigger; we can just use a normal button and open the Dialog manually. However Shadcn Dialog expects the trigger to be a DialogTrigger component; but we can also use the Dialog's open prop to control it programmatically. According to Radix UI, you can open the dialog programmatically by setting open prop to true. The DialogTrigger is optional; you can just use DialogContent with open prop.

Thus we can have:

